<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head>
<title>CSS Reference File</title>
<link href="mailto:rhauck@adobe.com" rel="author" title="Rebecca Hauck" />
    <style type="text/css">
        #container {
          position: absolute;
          top: 70px;
          width: 262px;
          height: 150px;
          border: 1px solid black;
        }
        #failure-container {

        }
        #margin-line {
            position: absolute;
            top: 100px;
            width: 263px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid black;
        }
        .fail {
            position: absolute;
            height: 15px;
            background-color: green;
            z-index: -1;
        }
        #bar-1 {
            top: 7px;
            left: 2px;
            width: 255px;
        }
        #bar-2 {
            top: 37px;
            left: 2px;
            width: 255px;
        }
        #bar-3 {
            top: 67px;
            left: 22px;
            width: 225px;
        }
        #bar-4 {
            top: 97px;
            left: 122px;
            width: 135px;
        }
        #bar-5 {
            top: 127px;
            left: 152px;
            width: 105px;
        }
       .triangle {
            position: absolute;
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            background-color: lightblue;
            clip-path: polygon(0% 50%, 50% 100%, 0 100%);;

        }
        #triangle-1 {
            top: 90px;
            margin-left: 2px;
        }
        #triangle-2 {
            top: 120px;
            margin-left: 102px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <p>
        The test passes if one green bar is inside the top rectangle, four green bars
        are in the bottom rectangle, and none intersect the triangles. There should be no
        red.
    </p>
    <div id="container">
        <div class="fail" id="bar-1"></div>
        <div class="fail" id="bar-2"></div>
        <div class="fail" id="bar-3"></div>
        <div class="fail" id="bar-4"></div>
        <div class="fail" id="bar-5"></div>
    </div>
    <div id="margin-line"></div>
    <div class="triangle" id="triangle-1"></div>
    <div class="triangle" id="triangle-2"></div>


</body></html>